// Fast-path slab allocator, per-P sharded. Pops a slot from the cached mspan in
// THIS P's mcache row (mcache_base + shard*144 + classIdx*8). The pop is
// lockless. On a miss (no cached span, or free_count == 0) it first drains this
// P's remote-free queue and re-probes; if still empty it refills (which takes
// __slab_lock) then pops. A successful pop that drains the span clears the
// mcache entry so the next call refills cleanly.
function __slab_alloc_class(classIdx MachineWord) returns MachineWord
