// Return a fully-emptied span to its class's mcentral partial list so a
// DIFFERENT P can later reclaim it. Runs entirely under the global __slab_lock.
// Steps: (1) span.owning_p = 0xFFFFFFFF sentinel; (2) prepend span to
// mcentral[classIdx].partial_head; (3) walk all 256 mcache rows and NULL any
// slot still pointing at this span (mostly defensive — the alloc-side evict
// already NULLs the owner's slot, but the 256-shard bound covers shard 0, the
// single-shard / pre-scheduler row).
function __slab_mcentral_return_span(span MachineWord)
