// Returns `slot` to its owning mspan's free list:
//   [slot] = mspan.free_list ; mspan.free_list = slot ; mspan.free_count += 1
// Common sink for every free path (same-P local push, fallback-local push, and
// the remote-free drain replay) — all reach here as the span's single writer,
// so the per-span mutation needs no lock. When this free brings free_count up
// to total_slots (+0x30) the span is fully empty and is handed back to mcentral
// (which takes __slab_lock internally).
