// Public allocator entry point. Routes >32768 to the OS-direct path (under
// __slab_lock, mutating the shared OS-direct array); otherwise scans the
// 18-class size table for the smallest class >= size and serves it from the
// calling P's own mcache row (lockless fast path; refill takes __slab_lock).
function __slab_alloc(size MachineWord) returns MachineWord
