// Allocate a tracked block of `size` bytes through the slab allocator.
// Layout: 32-byte mm header followed by the user region. The first header
// word sits at slot_base+0 so the destructor / size / refcount fields keep
// their historical `user_ptr - 24 / -16 / -8` offsets (every destructor and
// the COW path reads those, so leaving them put keeps the header layout
// stable). That word is reserved (always 0) — it preserves the trailing
// offsets without carrying any payload.
//   slot_base + 0  : reserved   (always 0)
//   slot_base + 8  : destructor (function pointer; 0 means "no destructor")
//   slot_base + 16 : size       (user-region size)
//   slot_base + 24 : refcount   (initialized to 0 — alloc-at-0 model, mirrors
//                                 the C# bootstrap: a fresh allocation owns NO
//                                 reference; the binding/field store that takes
//                                 ownership increfs it to 1. A value never bound
//                                 anywhere is freed at its producing scope's exit
//                                 decref of rc 0→... — see __mm_decref guard.)
//   user_ptr       = slot_base + 32 (returned)
function __mm_alloc(size MachineWord, destructor MachineWord) returns MachineWord
