// Release a tracked allocation. Reads the destructor from [ptr - 24] and
// invokes it (if non-null) before slab-freeing. The destructor is
// responsible for decreffing managed fields stored inside the user region;
// __mm_free only releases the surrounding allocation.
//
// Tolerates ptr == 0 as a no-op so callers don't have to null-check.
function __mm_free(ptr MachineWord)
