	// below copies raw slot POINTERS, so the new record must take its own +1 on
	// each live slot and inherit the source's element_destroy stamp — its
	// teardown walk then releases exactly the refs taken here. Without the
	// retain+stamp, the source's clear/teardown freed the shared elements under
	// the slice (the `Log.stopCapture` clone UAF that corrupted concurrent sort
	// data via slab-slot reuse) and the slice's own copies leaked.
