// Take +1 on each live (non-null) managed-pointer slot in `buffer[0, count)`.
// The retain mirror of `__managed_mem_walk_elements`: a record whose
// element_destroy is stamped (always `&__mm_decref` — managed-pointer
// elements) releases each slot once at teardown, so a helper that copies slot
// pointers into a walked buffer (`slice`, `append`) must take the matching +1
// here. Callers gate on `element_destroy != 0`, so a raw/primitive buffer is
// never walked (increfing a raw int would fault).
function __managed_mem_retain_range(buffer MachineWord, count MachineWord, elemSize MachineWord)
