	// into an OWNING container (an array literal's `Array.init(record)` transparent
	// wrap, a String, `mrt_read_stdin_managed`, …) whose field holds the lone reference
	// and whose destructor drops it once. `__mm_alloc` returns rc=0, and a transparent-
	// wrap/move owner supplies no field-store-incref, so without this the owner's single
	// decref goes 0->-1 and never frees → the record + buffer (+ any managed elements)
	// leak (the array-literal-of-Box leak). Mirrors `__managed_mem_slice` and the
	// lowering's `synthesizeManagedFieldInits` (both rc=1).
